{"title":"Video: Leah Lind-White Rips All Night On Kona Honzo ESD","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/02/kona-honza-esd-video/","date":1630610753000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div data-off-canvas-content=\"\"><main><img width=\"800\" height=\"505\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/02135944/Untitled-800x505.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs%3Adevice%2Frscb28-1\" alt=\"kona honzo esd lisa lind-white\" loading=\"eager\" srcset=\"\" sizes=\"\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\"><header></header></main><main role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-270262\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Work all day, party all night? That’s the formula as <a href=\"http://a%20steel%20frame%20holds%20a%20marzocchi%20bomber%20z1%20fork%20with%20150mm%20of%20travel.xn--%20its%20got%20strong%204-piston%20brakes%2C%20grippy%20maxxis%20rubber%2C%20and%20a%20headtube%20badge%20that%20will%20scare%20your%20children%20at%20night-dz05h.%20this%20is%20the%20warrior%20of%20the%20wasteland./\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Leah Lind-White</a> pulls an all-nighter with a self-aware <a href=\"https://www.konaworld.com/honzo_esd.cfm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Kona Honzo ESD</a>.</p><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ljpGRJlISeQ?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\" ezoid=\"0.9787219793248763\"></iframe></p><p>If you’re interested in the bike, it’s got a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/08/12/kona-honzo-esd-goes-from-test-mule-for-process-x-frame-geometry-to-extra-slack-steel-hardtail/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">steel frame</a> with wicked-cool violet metal flake paint, a <a href=\"https://www.marzocchi.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Marzocchi</a> Bomber Z1 fork with 150mm of travel, 4-piston brakes, and <a href=\"https://www.maxxis.com/us/tires/bicycle/mountain/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Maxxis rubber</a>. The finishing move? A chupacabra headtube badge that “will scare your children at night.” The vid might spook them, too; it’s not the least unsettling thing we’ve ever seen.</p><p>No need to quit your day job when you can rip trails all night and still answer the bell like Lind-White does.</p></section></article></main></div></div>","author":"Sam Anderson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"f75748cab80360302c00d530953b678ad3d4d2a3293ff6a2c44436c2db6a8769","category":"Cycling"}